# CDS-Responsive-Assist - Cursor AI Rules

## 🎯 MANDATORY: CDS is the Default Design System

**CRITICAL: When user provides ANY design request (prompt, Figma URL, screenshot, wireframe), you MUST automatically use CDS components and tokens. User never needs to mention "CDS" - it's ALWAYS the default.**

## Automatic Behavior

### User Says Anything → You Use CDS

| User Input | Your Automatic Response |
|------------|-------------------------|
| "Create a button" | Use CDS Button with proper variant and tokens |
| "Build a form" | Use CDS Container + Stack + TextField + LoadingButton |
| "Make a dashboard" | Use CDS AppBar + Drawer + Grid + Cards |
| "Design a card" | Use CDS Card with elevation and spacing tokens |
| Provides Figma URL | Fetch design, map to CDS components and tokens |
| Uploads screenshot | Analyze, recreate using CDS components |
| Shows wireframe | Implement with CDS components only |

**Never ask "Should I use CDS?" - Just use it automatically.**

## Translation Rules (Automatic)

### ANY Design Element → CDS Component

```typescript
// User says "button" → Automatic CDS translation
import Button from '@mui/material/Button';
<Button variant="contained" color="primary">Click Me</Button>

// User says "text input" → Automatic CDS translation
import TextField from '@mui/material/TextField';
<TextField label="Email" type="email" required fullWidth />

// User says "navigation" → Automatic CDS translation
import AppBar from '@mui/material/AppBar';
import Drawer from '@mui/material/Drawer';
// ... AppBar + Drawer pattern

// User says "card" → Automatic CDS translation
import Card from '@mui/material/Card';
<Card elevation={1}><CardContent>...</CardContent></Card>
```

## Figma/Screenshot → CDS Mapping (Automatic)

When user provides Figma URL or screenshot:

1. **Identify Elements**
   - Buttons → CDS Button (contained/outlined/text variant)
   - Text inputs → CDS TextField
   - Cards → CDS Card with elevation
   - Navigation → CDS AppBar/Drawer/BottomNavigation
   - Lists → CDS List or Table
   - Icons → @mui/icons-material

2. **Map Colors**
   - Blue buttons → `color="primary"` (palette.primary.main)
   - Red buttons → `color="error"` (palette.error.main)
   - Green success → `color="success"` (palette.success.main)
   - Custom colors → Map to closest CDS token

3. **Map Spacing**
   - 8px → `spacing(2)`
   - 12px → `spacing(3)`
   - 16px → `spacing(4)`
   - 24px → `spacing(6)`

4. **Map Typography**
   - Large headings → Typography variant="h3" or "h4"
   - Body text → Typography variant="body1"
   - Small text → Typography variant="body2" or "caption"

5. **Map Shadows**
   - Subtle shadow → `elevation={1}`
   - Medium shadow → `elevation={2}` or `elevation={4}`
   - Strong shadow → `elevation={8}`

## NEVER Do This

```tsx
// ❌ WRONG - Hard-coded values
<div style={{
  padding: '12px',
  backgroundColor: '#4b3fff',
  borderRadius: '4px'
}}>

// ❌ WRONG - Plain HTML
<button>Click</button>
<input type="text" />

// ❌ WRONG - Other libraries
import { Button } from 'bootstrap';
import { Button } from 'antd';
```

## ALWAYS Do This

```tsx
// ✅ CORRECT - CDS components with tokens
import Box from '@mui/material/Box';
<Box sx={{ 
  p: 3,                      // spacing token (12px)
  bgcolor: 'primary.main',   // color token
  borderRadius: 1            // radius token (4px)
}}>

// ✅ CORRECT - CDS components
import Button from '@mui/material/Button';
<Button variant="contained">Click</Button>

import TextField from '@mui/material/TextField';
<TextField label="Name" required />
```

## Code Generation Rules (Enforced Automatically)

### 1. Imports
```typescript
// ALWAYS import from @mui/material
import Button from '@mui/material/Button';
import TextField from '@mui/material/TextField';
import Card from '@mui/material/Card';
import Grid from '@mui/material/Grid';
import Typography from '@mui/material/Typography';

// Icons from @mui/icons-material
import HomeIcon from '@mui/icons-material/Home';
import SearchIcon from '@mui/icons-material/Search';
```

### 2. Styling with Tokens
```typescript
// ALWAYS use sx prop with theme tokens
<Box sx={{
  p: 3,                       // spacing(3) = 12px
  mt: 2,                      // margin-top: spacing(2) = 8px
  bgcolor: 'primary.main',    // color token
  color: 'primary.contrastText',
  borderRadius: 1,            // 4px
  elevation: 1                // subtle shadow
}}>
```

### 3. Typography
```typescript
// ALWAYS use Typography component
<Typography variant="h4" gutterBottom>
  Title
</Typography>
<Typography variant="body1" color="text.secondary">
  Description
</Typography>

// NEVER use plain HTML
// ❌ <h1>Title</h1>
// ❌ <p>Description</p>
```

### 4. Responsive Design
```typescript
// ALWAYS use breakpoint objects (mobile-first)
<Grid container spacing={3}>
  <Grid item xs={12} sm={6} md={4}>
    {/* Mobile: full width
        Tablet: half width
        Desktop: one-third width */}
  </Grid>
</Grid>

// Or responsive sx props
<Box sx={{
  p: { xs: 2, sm: 3, md: 4 },        // 8px, 12px, 16px
  fontSize: { xs: '14px', md: '16px' }
}}>
```

### 5. Accessibility (Built-in)
```typescript
// ALWAYS include ARIA attributes
<TextField
  label="Email"
  required
  aria-required="true"
  aria-describedby="email-helper"
  helperText="Enter your email address"
/>

<Button
  variant="contained"
  aria-label="Submit form"
  disabled={isLoading}
>
  Submit
</Button>

// ALWAYS meet touch target minimum (48px)
<IconButton size="large"> {/* Ensures 48px minimum */}
  <DeleteIcon />
</IconButton>
```

## Common Patterns (Use Automatically)

### Login Form
```typescript
import Container from '@mui/material/Container';
import Stack from '@mui/material/Stack';
import TextField from '@mui/material/TextField';
import LoadingButton from '@mui/lab/LoadingButton';
import Alert from '@mui/material/Alert';

<Container maxWidth="xs">
  <Stack spacing={3}>
    <Typography variant="h4">Sign In</Typography>
    {error && <Alert severity="error">{error}</Alert>}
    <TextField label="Email" type="email" required fullWidth />
    <TextField label="Password" type="password" required fullWidth />
    <LoadingButton variant="contained" loading={isLoading} fullWidth>
      Sign In
    </LoadingButton>
  </Stack>
</Container>
```

### Dashboard Layout
```typescript
import AppBar from '@mui/material/AppBar';
import Drawer from '@mui/material/Drawer';
import Grid from '@mui/material/Grid';
import Card from '@mui/material/Card';

<>
  <AppBar position="fixed" elevation={4}>
    <Toolbar>{/* Header content */}</Toolbar>
  </AppBar>
  <Drawer variant="permanent" elevation={16}>
    <List>{/* Navigation */}</List>
  </Drawer>
  <Box component="main" sx={{ p: 3 }}>
    <Grid container spacing={3}>
      <Grid item xs={12} sm={6} md={3}>
        <Card elevation={1}>{/* Stat card */}</Card>
      </Grid>
    </Grid>
  </Box>
</>
```

### Data Table
```typescript
import Paper from '@mui/material/Paper';
import Table from '@mui/material/Table';
import Pagination from '@mui/material/Pagination';

<Paper elevation={1}>
  <Table>
    <TableHead>
      <TableRow>
        <TableCell>Name</TableCell>
        <TableCell>Email</TableCell>
      </TableRow>
    </TableHead>
    <TableBody>
      {data.map(row => (
        <TableRow key={row.id}>
          <TableCell>{row.name}</TableCell>
          <TableCell>{row.email}</TableCell>
        </TableRow>
      ))}
    </TableBody>
  </Table>
</Paper>
<Pagination count={totalPages} page={page} />
```

### User Profile Card
```typescript
import Card from '@mui/material/Card';
import Avatar from '@mui/material/Avatar';
import Badge from '@mui/material/Badge';

<Card elevation={1}>
  <CardHeader
    avatar={
      <Badge badgeContent={4} color="error">
        <Avatar src={user.avatar}>{user.initials}</Avatar>
      </Badge>
    }
    action={<IconButton><MoreVertIcon /></IconButton>}
    title={user.name}
    subheader={user.role}
  />
  <CardContent>
    <Typography variant="body2" color="text.secondary">
      {user.bio}
    </Typography>
  </CardContent>
</Card>
```

## CDS Token Reference (Quick Lookup)

### Colors (CDS Brand)
```typescript
color="primary"              // #4b3fff (CDS Primary Blue)
color="secondary"            // #dc004e (CDS Secondary Purple/Pink)
color="error"                // #d32f2f (CDS Error Red)
color="success"              // #2e7d32 (CDS Success Green)
color="warning"              // #ed6c02 (CDS Warning Orange)
color="info"                 // #0288d1 (CDS Info Blue)

sx={{ color: 'text.primary' }}      // rgba(0,0,0,0.87)
sx={{ color: 'text.secondary' }}    // rgba(0,0,0,0.6)
sx={{ bgcolor: 'background.paper' }} // #ffffff
```

### Spacing
```typescript
spacing={2}      // 8px gap
spacing={3}      // 12px gap
spacing={4}      // 16px gap

sx={{ p: 2 }}    // 8px padding
sx={{ p: 3 }}    // 12px padding
sx={{ mt: 2 }}   // 8px margin-top
sx={{ mb: 4 }}   // 16px margin-bottom
```

### Typography
```typescript
variant="h1"     // 96px, 300 weight
variant="h2"     // 60px, 300 weight
variant="h3"     // 48px, 400 weight
variant="h4"     // 34px, 400 weight (common for page titles)
variant="h5"     // 24px, 400 weight
variant="h6"     // 20px, 500 weight
variant="body1"  // 16px, 400 weight (default body)
variant="body2"  // 14px, 400 weight (secondary text)
variant="button" // 14px, 500 weight, uppercase
variant="caption" // 12px, 400 weight (helper text)
```

### Elevation
```typescript
elevation={0}    // Flat, no shadow
elevation={1}    // Subtle (cards at rest)
elevation={2}    // Raised
elevation={4}    // App bar default
elevation={8}    // Floating buttons, bottom nav
elevation={16}   // Drawer
elevation={24}   // Maximum (tooltips)
```

### Responsive Breakpoints
```typescript
xs: 0px          // Mobile portrait (default)
sm: 600px        // Mobile landscape / Tablet portrait
md: 900px        // Tablet landscape
lg: 1200px       // Desktop
xl: 1536px       // Large desktop

// Usage:
<Grid item xs={12} sm={6} md={4} lg={3}>
<Box sx={{ p: { xs: 2, md: 4 } }}>
```

## Component Quick Reference

### Navigation
- **AppBar** - Top navigation bar
- **Drawer** - Side navigation panel
- **BottomNavigation** - Mobile bottom tabs
- **Menu** - Dropdown menus
- **Tabs** - Tabbed content

### Inputs
- **TextField** - Text input
- **Checkbox** - Checkbox
- **Radio** - Radio button
- **Switch** - Toggle switch
- **Select** - Dropdown select
- **Slider** - Range slider

### Buttons
- **Button** - Standard button
- **IconButton** - Icon-only button
- **FAB** - Floating action button
- **LoadingButton** - Button with loading state

### Layout
- **Container** - Max-width wrapper
- **Grid** - 12-column grid
- **Stack** - Vertical/horizontal stack
- **Box** - Generic container

### Display
- **Card** - Content card
- **Paper** - Elevated surface
- **Typography** - Text
- **Avatar** - User avatar
- **Badge** - Notification badge
- **List** - List of items
- **Table** - Data table

### Feedback
- **Alert** - Alert messages
- **Snackbar** - Toast notifications
- **Dialog** - Modal dialog
- **Skeleton** - Loading placeholder
- **CircularProgress** - Loading spinner
- **LinearProgress** - Progress bar

## Accessibility Checklist (Auto-Applied)

✅ Keyboard navigation (Tab, Enter, Space, Arrows)
✅ ARIA attributes (aria-label, aria-describedby)
✅ Color contrast (4.5:1 text, 3:1 non-text)
✅ Touch targets (48px minimum)
✅ Focus indicators (visible)
✅ Screen reader support (semantic HTML)
✅ Error messages (clear, associated with inputs)

## Quality Enforcement

- ✅ 100% CDS component usage
- ✅ 100% token usage (no hard-coded values)
- ✅ 100% WCAG 2.1 AA compliance
- ✅ 100% responsive (mobile-first)
- ✅ 100% TypeScript

## User Experience

**User provides:** Just a prompt, Figma URL, or screenshot
**You automatically:** Map to CDS and generate production-ready code
**Result:** CDS-compliant, accessible, responsive code - no CDS mention needed

---

**Remember: CDS is ALWAYS the default. User never needs to mention it.**
